 the proposal's strength.\n\n**Next Steps:**\n1. **Identify Potential Reviewers:**\n   - Reach out to colleagues and fellow researchers in recommender systems and machine learning.\n   - Consult with academic advisors or mentors.\n   - Engage with industry professionals in e-commerce, streaming services, and social media platforms.\n\n2. **Share the Proposal:**\n   - Send the proposal via email.\n   - Use collaboration tools like Google Docs or Microsoft Word Online.\n   - Present the proposal at relevant conferences or workshops.\n\n3. **Request Specific Feedback:**\n   - Comment on the clarity of research questions, methodology, and significance.\n   - Inquire about the feasibility of the proposed approach.\n   - Seek input on the relevance and potential impact of the research.\n   - Request suggestions for improvements.\n\n4. **Collect and Organize Feedback:**\n   - Gather all feedback.\n   - Categorize comments into methodology, significance, literature review, and overall structure.\n\n5. **Refine the Proposal:**\n   - Incorporate feedback to address concerns and suggestions.\n   - Revise sections like literature review, methodology, and significance.\n   - Clarify any ambiguities.\n\n6. **Iterate if Necessary:**\n   - Go through multiple rounds of feedback and refinement.\n   - Consider conducting pilot studies to validate methodology.\n\n**Example Email for Seeking Feedback:**\n- **Subject:** Feedback Request for Research Proposal on Evaluating Sequential Recommender Systems\n- **Body:** A detailed email is provided to request feedback from reviewers, emphasizing the importance of their insights in refining the proposal.\n\n**Outcome:**\nThe conversation highlights the importance of seeking and incorporating feedback to strengthen the research proposal. The outlined steps provide a structured approach to achieving this goal, ensuring the proposal meets high standards and is well-received in the academic and industry communities."}
