erature review, methodology, and significance.\\n   - Clarify any ambiguities.\\n\\n6. **Iterate if Necessary:**\\n   - Go through multiple rounds of feedback and refinement.\\n   - Consider conducting pilot studies to validate methodology.\\n\\n**Example Email for Seeking Feedback:**\\n- **Subject:** Feedback Request for Research Proposal on Evaluating Sequential Recommender Systems\\n- **Body:** A detailed email is provided to request feedback from reviewers, emphasizing the importance of their insights in refining the proposal.\\n\\n**Outcome:**\\nThe conversation highlights the importance of seeking and incorporating feedback to strengthen the research proposal. The outlined steps provide a structured approach to achieving this goal, ensuring the proposal meets high standards and is well-received in the academic and industry communities."}'}, {'agent6': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": true, "message": "Successfully completed session 2eac6f04-ab8d-4a09-b0a2-47c0816ca812", "full_chat_history": "In Session 2eac6f04-ab8d-4a09-b0a2-47c0816ca812 \\nFrom agent6 to agent7: Here is the draft methodology section for the research proposal on evaluating datasets in Sequential Recommender Systems. Could you provide feedback on the metrics, models, dataset curation, and evaluation protocols?\\n\\n#### Metrics and Models\\nTo assess the strength of sequential patterns in datasets, we will use a combination of metrics and models. The metrics will include sequential rule identification, model performance on shuffled vs. unshuffled data, temporal coherence measures, and entropy of sequences. The models will include SASRec, GRU4Rec, and other relevant models such as BERT4Rec and CDIMF.\\n\\n#### Dataset Curation\\nWe will curate a diverse set of datasets specifically designed to test the performance of Sequential Recommender Systems (SRSs). The criteria for inclusion will be datasets with well-defined sequential patterns, from diverse domains such as 